exec() - when exec system call is invoked the {programm defined in the parameter to  exec() } will replace the entire process.- including all thread
            the parameter passed to exec() sysytem call will be another program,so when we pass a program as a parameter the programm will replace the entire process 				throw which the new programm called
            
            replacing a process with new process , process id remains same.
            
2.  execl("/bin/ls","ls","-l",0);    here this will replace the cureent process with new process ( ls )
								"/bin/ls"is he 1st argument is the location of the program
								"ls" is the name of process/program
								"-l" from 3rd argument onwards it will be the options that you want to use
								0 for null means np more arguments
